    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="content">
                <div type="leiden">
                <cit type="interpretive">
                    <quote>none</quote>
                </cit>
                <cit type="diplomatic">
                    <quote>none</quote>
                </cit>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <unclear>α</unclear>βγ = ̣αβγ<!-- the dot should be left like this -->
                    <damage>α</damage>βγ = αβγ
                </egXML>
                <p>Stretches of ambiguous text that span words, lines, names, dates, or other tagged features, should be marked with multiple <gi>unclear</gi> elements.</p>
                <p>Sigillographic habits do not include the underdot in the editorial interpretation, but only in the diplomatic edition, for which, however, Athena Ruby’s underdot should be used; hence, <gi>unclear</gi> and <gi>damage</gi> are not really necessary.</p>
                <p>For lost characters, see <gi>gap</gi>.</p>
            </div>
